class Solution {
    public List<String> removeSubfolders(String[] folder) {
        Arrays.sort(folder);
        List<String> res = new ArrayList<>();
        String prev = "";
        for (String f : folder) {
            if (prev.isEmpty() || !f.startsWith(prev) || f.charAt(prev.length()) != '/') {
                res.add(f);
                prev = f;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N log N)
space complexity: O(N)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Sort the paths lexicographically so every parent folder appears before its sub-folders. Iterate once, adding a folder only if it is not a sub-folder of the last kept folder (checked via prefix match and a trailing '/'). This avoids building a trie and uses only sorting plus a single pass.

